Min resa och varför jag valde att bli 1-1 coach. 

För mig handlar inte träning och kost bara om utseendet. Det var så förr, men idag har jag insett att värdet bakom det är så mycket mer än att bara se bra ut för andra. Vi människor har en tendens att vilja imponera på andra-såklart, men ibland glömmer vi bort oss själva i det. Det är exempelvis inte hållbart att deffa genom att äta alldeles för lite mat varje dag och konstant gå runt och vara orkeslös. Visst - du kanske får komplimanger för att du ser definierad ut, men vad är det för liv att leva? Hungrig? Konstant orkeslös? Det är absolut inget liv jag vill leva. Hade det sättet varit det enda sättet för att bli rippad på så hade jag varit tyst, för vissa personer prioriterar olika och vill man vara rippad så är det klart man ska vara det. MEN! Det är inte det enda sättet och nu pratar jag helt utifrån egen erfarenhet. Bara titta på min jämförelsebild. Att vara restriktiv med kosten är inget som behövs för att få sin drömkropp, det gäller bara att vara smart. 

Kost och träning handlar för mig om att kunna styrka över sitt eget välmående. Att känna sig stark. Att känna sig motiverad. Att känna sig trygg i sig själv. Att vakna upp på morgonen och känna sig pigg, redo att ta an dagen oavsett vad som väntar. 

Utseendet är det vi tror att vi alla strävar efter, men innerst inne tror jag det är mer än så. Alla människor strävar efter välmående och lycka. När vi har uppnått det, har vi enligt mig lyckats i livet. Utseendet som din kropp får under resan är bara en bonus. ⚡️

believe me i am the FIRST person to force feed you protein 🫣 you should be eating around 0.8–1g of protein per 1lb of body weight if you want to see results 

here’s the thing — hitting your protein goal with a bunch of processed junk is NOT the way !!! like yea protein powders/bars/shakes/puddings can totally help sometimes (i literally love my protein pudding bowls), but they should only be a small portion of your daily intake !! 

when i first started caring about protein, i didn’t know the difference in quality — i thought all protein was created equal. if a package said “high protein” it was in my cart ! but after living off processed snacks (esp when i was vegan), i was always bloated, never satisfied, and honestly not seeing the results i wanted 

the key is structuring your day around real, whole food protein sources:
• breakfast: 20–30g (eggs, egg whites, lean chicken sausage, cottage cheese, greek yogurt)
• lunch: 30g (chicken, steak, fish, shrimp, ground turkey/beef)
• snack: 15–20g (turkey slices, cottage cheese, shredded chicken, protein shake)
• dinner: 30g (chicken, steak, fish, shrimp, ground turkey/beef)
• dessert: 15–20g (greek yogurt, protein pudding, creami)

that adds up to 110–130g without relying fully on packaged protein 

if you wanna see results and feel good 👇🏼
✨ real meals with whole food protein
✨ enough fiber, carbs & fats (cutting too much makes you bloated)
✨ supplements only when needed

real food >>> processed food always !!!! 🤍

i’m a firm believer that all foods can fit into a healthy diet and still help you hit your goals. but here’s the thing… there’s a big difference between CAN and SHOULD 🙃

if these are staples in your day to day, it might be time to cut back, swap them for better alternatives, and add in foods that will actually move you toward your goals instead of away from them 👇🏼

✨ flavored yogurt — “but it’s high protein!”… and also loaded with 20g of sugar. stick to plain greek yogurt and add stevia drops, cinnamon, fruit, or fun toppings. save those sugars for something you actually want to indulge in

✨ store bought granola — literal sugar in a bag. even the “clean” ones usually sneak in way too much sugar by only using ‘date’ or ‘coconut sugar.’ just make your own at home 🫶🏼

✨ wheat based cereals — basically a bowl of sugar + milk to start your day. zero nutritional value and you’ll be hungry again in 10 minutes (if you love cereal, @threewishescereal or @catalinacrunch always !!!) 

✨ restaurant salads — amazing choice… if you’re mindful. most come drowning in 500 calories worth of dressing + croutons, fried toppings, excess nuts, and seeds. don’t just pick what you believe to be healthy… make sure it actually is 

✨ alcohol — even a “clean” vodka soda is ~100 calories. 3 drinks in, you may as well have the milkshake you’re actually craving. alcohol stops fat burning completely while your liver processes it & drinking usually flips the switch to late night, uncontrolled snacking 

so here’s the hard truth — you can train abs all day, juice cleanse all week, but if you’re not fueling your body properly with nutrition… you’re just sabotaging your results 

be smart. be mindful. be intentional. see the results you’re working so hard for 🤍

caption:
TOP TIPS FOR STRAIGHT LEG CABLE KICKBACKS 💁‍♀️✨

I hear a lot of the time “I can only feel this in my standing leg🫠” or “my lower back hurts🥴”

Give the tips a go that have helped me and let me know how it goes!!! 🍑

✅ Have cable about knee height - this allows you to extend your leg forward to get into the lengthening stretch of the glute, to then engage it more when you kickback! 🥳
✅ Stand on a plate - this really helps to avoid catching the floor when doing the kickbacks, no need to stress about that any more!😮‍💨
✅ Turn working foot out to a 45 degree angle & Keep foot flat - will help to target the peach more! 📐
✅ Imagine driving through your heel while tending the booty cheek - will help your mind to muscle connection ✨
✅ Pause at the top and stay in control of the movement - this is super important to help activate the glute muscles more during this exercise ✋🛑
✅ Keep hips facing forward and engage your core - will help you to actually use the glute muscles and reduce pull through the back!🫶🏼
✅ Lean only at a slight angle and find hand positioning to support you! - this really helps to take the pressure off the lower back😮‍💨
✅ Kick out at a slight angle - this will help to target your glute medius more ✨

Remember girlie, take your time, go light at first and get the correct & effective form before upping the weight 💖
